document.full_text: oil prices eased on wednesday in choppy, thin trading, pressured by record high stockpiles at the cushing delivery point for u.s. crude even as libya and middle east uncertainty supported oil, which remained on track to end the first-quarter up more than 10 percent.
document.title: oil slips on inventory rise, supply threats support
